        <div class="seo-card"><h3>Do I need a fence permit in Toledo, Ohio?</h3><p>Yes, Toledo requires a <strong>Certificate of Zoning Compliance</strong> (ZONING permit, not building permit) for ALL fences regardless of height. Front yard maximum is 3.5 feet (open style only), side and rear yards allow up to 6 feet. The permit is free but approval is required before installation.</p></div>
        <div class="seo-card"><h3>Zoning Permit vs Building Permit - What's the difference?</h3><p>A <strong>ZONING permit</strong> verifies your fence meets location, height, and setback rules. A <strong>BUILDING permit</strong> verifies construction meets safety codes. Most Ohio cities require ZONING permits for fences. Michigan cities typically require BUILDING permits.</p></div>
        <div class="seo-card"><h3>Do I need a fence permit in Perrysburg Township?</h3><p>Perrysburg Township is <strong>PARTIALLY ZONED</strong>. Some areas require a Zoning Certificate ($25-$50) and some do not. Call the Zoning Department at (419) 874-3551 ext. 4005 to verify if your property is in a zoned area. Fences may be up to 7 feet in height!</p></div>
        <div class="seo-card"><h3>What is the maximum fence height in Ohio?</h3><p>Most Ohio municipalities allow <strong>4 feet in front yards</strong> (open style - 50%+ open) and <strong>6 feet in side/rear yards</strong> (privacy fences OK). Some areas like Toledo limit front yards to 3.5 feet.</p></div>
        <div class="seo-card"><h3>Do I need a fence permit in Monroe, Michigan?</h3><p>Yes, Monroe MI requires a <strong>BUILDING permit</strong> ($50-$100). This is different from Ohio where zoning permits are more common. Michigan has stricter building code requirements. Call MISS DIG 811 before digging.</p></div>
        <div class="seo-card"><h3>What are corner lot fence rules?</h3><p>Corner lots have <strong>"sight triangle"</strong> restrictions - an area near intersections where fences must be shorter (usually 2.5-3ft max) so drivers can see. The triangle is typically 20-25 feet from the corner along each street.</p></div>
